Progress
--------

- (10/03/2026) Exercises 1вЂ“3 completed (introduction, stack understanding, semantics)
- (12/03/2026) Implemented AST and evaluation of expressions (exercise 4)
- (14/03/2026) Implemented lexer and parser for Expr (exercise 5)
- (17/03/2026) Parser fully working and tested with multiple expressions (exercise 6)
- (18/03/2026) Modified lexer files to return the location of errors (exercise 7)
- (19/03/2026) Implemented and validated a test suite for the Pfx VM
- (13/04/2026) Exercise 9.3 вЂ“ Modifications :
    AST: added Code, Exec, Get
    Lexer: added tokens ( ) exec get + error locations
    Parser: added executable sequences ( ... ) and new commands
    Stack: changed to heterogeneous (VInt | VCode)
    Eval: implemented semantics for Code, Exec, Get
    Tests: validated with dune exec pfx/pfxVM.exe

===============

How to test

Quick testing from terminal:

  echo "<expression>" > test.expr && dune exec expr/main.exe test.expr
  dune exec expr/main.exe test.expr

Examples to test:

  3+4
  3+4*5
  (3+4)*5
  -(5+2)

Exercice 9.3:
  dune exec pfx/pfxVM.exe pfx/basic/tests/9.3_test.pfx
